Another option I have used in the past was to create a temp table for the new and old key and select in the old key and a generated new key. Then I do my insert into the target table by joining the source table and this key table, followed by updating the source table from the key table. It&#039;s slightly more moving pieces and if you have IDENTITY columns you have to turn them off and reseed them when you&#039;re done, but it does get the job done.

